        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-21 18:45:13.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\n> So if you update the controller policy, eg new version, then you\n > have to find all policies that reference it and update them also so\n > they point to the latest (same) version?\n\nThis is a good point. Maybe we can just put controllerVersion optional so that it will be assigned to the latest version always",
